# Build context is the repo root (bun.lock is a workspace lockfile and only
# exists here), so everything below would otherwise be shipped to the daemon.

# Host node_modules contain platform-native binaries (oxlint, turbo, rollup,
# tailwind oxide). Leaking darwin-arm64 builds into a linux image breaks `vite build`.
node_modules
**/node_modules

# Build output — always rebuilt inside the image
dist
**/dist
bin
**/bin
.turbo
**/.turbo
*.tsbuildinfo
**/*.tsbuildinfo

# Secrets. Bun auto-loads .env from cwd, which would silently shadow the
# environment Compose injects.
.env
**/.env
.env.*
**/.env.*
!.env.example
!**/.env.example

# Leftover local database artifact
**/*.sqlite

.git
.gitignore
.github
.vscode
.DS_Store
**/.DS_Store

Dockerfile
**/Dockerfile
.dockerignore
docker-compose*.yml

docs
README.md
**/README.md
LICENSE
**/LICENSE
install.sh
coverage
*.lcov
*.tgz
